3.2.0 -- 9 Aug 2012
-----
Arne.Wiebalck@cern.ch: Remove cache devices SCSI-wise before replacement, 
                       otherwise dm/flashcache will continue draining
		       IOs to it and crash the kernel when the device is
		       replaced.

3.1.0 -- 8 Aug 2012
-----
Arne.Wiebalck@cern.ch: Removed sysctls as they're not properly unregistered
                       and can caused kernel OOPSes.

3.0.0 -- 3 Aug 2012
-----
Arne.Wiebalck@cern.ch: Added capability to hot replace cache devices.
                       See src/utils/flashcache_replace.

2.0.1 -- 24 May 2012
-----
Arne.Wiebalck@cern.ch: Addded Changelog. 

2.0.0 
-----
Arne Wiebalck@cern.ch: Added wt superblock (at the end of the cache device).
                       Introduced version numbers (major.minor.revision).

1.0.0
-----
Arne.Wiebalck@cern.ch: Added BYPASS mode.
